so there's lots in literature.
There are also settings which

00:36:02.137 --> 00:36:04.280
aren't exactly out of
literature.

00:36:04.280 --> 00:36:08.699
So one example would be in a
bike race.

00:36:08.699 --> 00:36:11.219
How many of you ever watch the
Tour de France?

00:36:11.219 --> 00:36:12.480
Everyone know what I mean by
the Tour de France.

00:36:12.480 --> 00:36:15.490
So this is a bike race that
goes around France.

00:36:15.490 --> 00:36:18.992
It takes stages.
And in the Tour de France,

00:36:18.992 --> 00:36:22.103
there's a key decision.
There's a game within the game,

00:36:22.103 --> 00:36:24.914
and the game within the
game--I'm looking at Jake who's

00:36:24.914 --> 00:36:27.985
a real cyclist here--but the
game within the game is when do

00:36:27.985 --> 00:36:30.120
you try to break away from the
pack,

00:36:30.120 --> 00:36:33.189
which is called the peloton.
And if you break away too early

00:36:33.189 --> 00:36:35.645
from the peloton,
it turns out that you're going

00:36:35.645 --> 00:36:38.123
to get reeled in.
It turns out that over the long

00:36:38.123 --> 00:36:40.250
haul the peloton can go much
faster than you.

00:36:40.250 --> 00:36:42.960
So if you break too early
they're going to catch you up.

00:36:42.960 --> 00:36:44.620
On the other hand,
if you break too late,

00:36:44.620 --> 00:36:46.862
then you're going to lose
because there are going to be

00:36:46.862 --> 00:36:49.519
some people in the peloton who
are just excellent sprinters.

00:36:49.519 --> 00:36:52.875
So if you break too late the
sprinters are going to win the

00:36:52.875 --> 00:36:55.200
race.
So you have to decide when to

00:36:55.200 --> 00:36:58.193
break from the peloton.
This is the second most

00:36:58.193 --> 00:37:01.245
important game within a game in
the Tour de France,

00:37:01.245 --> 00:37:04.785
the most important game within
a game is where to hide your

00:37:04.785 --> 00:37:09.393
steroids.
So let me give you one other

00:37:09.393 --> 00:37:12.033
example.
Let me give you a more economic

00:37:12.033 --> 00:37:14.159
example--it's meant to be an
economics class.

00:37:14.159 --> 00:37:17.325
Imagine there's two firms,
and these two firms are both

00:37:17.325 --> 00:37:20.079
engaged in R&amp;D,
research and development.

00:37:20.079 --> 00:37:23.578
And they're trying to develop a
new product, and they're going

00:37:23.578 --> 00:37:26.159
to launch this new product onto
the market.

00:37:26.159 --> 00:37:28.861
But the nature of this market
is--maybe it's a network

00:37:28.861 --> 00:37:32.021
good--the nature of this market
is there's only going to be one

00:37:32.021 --> 00:37:34.852
successful good out there.
So essentially there's going to

00:37:34.852 --> 00:37:36.702
be one standard,
let's say of a software or a

00:37:36.702 --> 00:37:38.887
technological standard,
and only one of them is going

00:37:38.887 --> 00:37:40.980
to survive.
The problem is you haven't

00:37:40.980 --> 00:37:44.596
perfected your product yet.
If you launch your product too

00:37:44.596 --> 00:37:48.072
early it may not work,
and then consumers are never

00:37:48.072 --> 00:37:51.348
going to trust you again.
But if you launch it too late

00:37:51.348 --> 00:37:53.227
the other side will have
launched already,

00:37:53.227 --> 00:37:56.159
they will have got a toehold in
the market, and you're toast.

00:37:56.159 --> 00:38:00.391
So that game--that game about
product launch--is like duel,

00:38:00.391 --> 00:38:04.477
except you're launching a
product rather than launching a

00:38:04.477 --> 00:38:06.800
sponge.
Is that right?

00:38:06.800 --> 00:38:09.301
Now all of these games have a
common feature,

00:38:09.301 --> 00:38:12.590
and it's a new feature for us.
It's about the nature of the

00:38:12.590 --> 00:38:15.118
strategic decision.
In most of the games we've

00:38:15.118 --> 00:38:18.588
looked at in the course so far
the strategic decision has been

00:38:18.588 --> 00:38:20.750
of the form: where should I
locate,

00:38:20.750 --> 00:38:23.680
how much should I do,
what price should I set,

00:38:23.680 --> 00:38:26.090
should I stand for election or
not?

00:38:26.090 --> 00:38:31.943
Here the strategic decision is
not of the form what should I

00:38:31.943 --> 00:38:33.970
do.
It's of the form what?

00:38:33.970 --> 00:38:37.343
When?
It's of the form when am

00:38:37.343 --> 00:38:40.188
I going to launch the sponge?
We know perfectly well what

00:38:40.188 --> 00:38:41.850
you're going to do.
You're going to throw the

00:38:41.850 --> 00:38:44.251
sponge.
The strategic issue in question

00:38:44.251 --> 00:38:47.570
is when.
So the issue here is when.

00:38:53.050 --> 00:38:54.985
So to analyze this,
I'm going to need a little bit

00:38:54.985 --> 00:38:57.000
of notation, and let me put that
notation up now.

00:38:57.000 --> 00:39:02.412
So in particular,
